-- Real Madrid Plans $46 Million Ashley Cole Transfer, Sun Says: Roundup
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-07-14T11:03:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/real-madrid-plans-46-million-ashley-cole-transfer-sun-says-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  
 Cole’s Transfer  
 Chelsea defender  Ashley Cole  is set to join Real Madrid for
30 million pounds ($45.8 million) after four years with the
London club,  the Sun  reported.  
 Madrid goalkeeper  Iker Casillas  said the “signs look
good” as coach  Jose Mourinho  seeks to lure Cole, according to
the Sun.  
 Chelsea Targets  
 Chelsea pulled out of the race to sign Germany’s Werder
Bremen midfielder Mesut Ozil, who is likely to join Bayern
Munich,  the Sun  said.  
 The Blues still want to sign Stuttgart midfielder  Sami Khedira  and is interested in Portugal defender Fabio Coentrao
and Spain winger Pedro, the Sun reported.  
 Mascherano Move  
 Liverpool midfielder  Javier Mascherano  wants to join former
Reds coach  Rafael Benitez  at Inter Milan, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  
 The Argentine is attracted to playing with compatriots like
 Diego Milito  for the “the strongest team in the world,”
Mascherano’s agent Walter Tamer was quoted as saying.  
 Liverpool Trade  
 Liverpool coach  Roy Hodgson  plans a 6-million pound bid for
Monaco’s South Korean forward Park Chu-Young,  the Sun  reported.
Park scored against Nigeria at the World Cup.  
